OWERRI  – Worried by the growing rate of unemployment and crime wave across the country, the traditional ruler of Isiokpo Autonomous Community in Ideato North Council Area of Imo State, Eze Raphael Amanze Offonze has called for speedy resuscitation of moribund industries in the country. According to the Monarch, bringing such ailing and decadent institutions back to life would not only improve the nation’s wobbling economy, but also provide jobs for the teeming jobless youths, in addition to reducing youths restiveness and insecurity in the land. Eze Offonze, who is the Ezedke II of Isiokpo and the patron of the Orlu Zuru Mee Organisation made the observation during the 2020 Edition of his annual thanksgiving empowerment scheme held at his Green Garden Palace otherwise known as the garden of Hope and magic of rural development. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! “Our leaders should rise up and do more in their poverty alleviation programs so as to engage the youths in meaningful ventures and also to stem the disturbing trend of insecurity and youth restiveness in the land”. The traditional ruler- a reputable industrialist lamented that more than 15 industries in his area had gone out of business, thereby escalating youth unemployment, stressing that a timely revival and reactivation of such industries now lying comatose would put smiles on the faces of the people. China To Overtake United States As World’s Biggest Economy In 2028 Woman Escapes Mob Action Over False Claim Of Missing Money In Onitsha The royal father explained that his yearly women and youth empowerment package which began 15 years ago was meant to cushion the plight of the poor and the needy in society, adding that he had equally established a care centre for senior citizens in his domain which among other things, issues free medical services to them. SH